Exp No: 20 Name of Experiment : File Uploading Using PHP (To Understand File Uploading in PHP) 
Aim: To upload the user input file and using constraints file type, file size.

INPUT:
UPLOAD_FORM.HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>File Upload</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 400px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        .form-group {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .form-group label {
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }
        .form-group input[type="file"] {
            width: 100%;
        }
        .form-group input[type="submit"] {
            background-color: #5cb85c;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        .form-group input[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #4cae4c;
        }
        .message {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        .error {
            color: #d9534f;
            background-color: #f2dede;
        }
        .success {
            color: #3c763d;
            background-color: #dff0d8;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Select File to Upload</h1>
        <form action="upload_file.php" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="fileToUpload">Choose file:</label>
                <input type="file" name="fileToUpload" id="fileToUpload">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <input type="submit" value="Upload">
            </div>
        </form>
        <?php
        if (isset($_GET['message'])) {
            $message = htmlspecialchars($_GET['message']);
            $status = htmlspecialchars($_GET['status']);
            echo "<div class='message $status'>$message</div>";
        }
        ?>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
UPLOAD_FILE.PHP
<?php
$target_dir = "GEUPHP/"; 

if (!is_dir($target_dir)) {
    mkdir($target_dir, 0777, true); 
}

$target_file = $target_dir . basename($_FILES["fileToUpload"]["name"]);
$uploadOk = 1;
$message = "";
$status = "error";

if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    // Check if file was uploaded without errors
    if (isset($_FILES["fileToUpload"]) && $_FILES["fileToUpload"]["error"] == 0) {
        $file_type = strtolower(pathinfo($target_file, PATHINFO_EXTENSION));
        $allowed_types = array("jpg", "png", "jpeg", "gif", "pdf", "txt", "doc", "docx");
        $max_file_size = 2 * 1024 * 1024; // 2MB

        // Check file size
        if ($_FILES["fileToUpload"]["size"] > $max_file_size) {
            $message = "Sorry, your file is too large. Max size is 2MB.";
            $uploadOk = 0;
        }

        // Check file type
        if (!in_array($file_type, $allowed_types)) {
            $message = "Invalid file extension!";
            $uploadOk = 0;
        }

        // Check if $uploadOk is set to 0 by an error
        if ($uploadOk == 0) {
            $status = "error";
        } else {
            // Try to upload file
            if (move_uploaded_file($_FILES["fileToUpload"]["tmp_name"], $target_file)) {
                $message = "The file " . htmlspecialchars(basename($_FILES["fileToUpload"]["name"])) . " has been uploaded.";
                $status = "success";
            } else {
                $message = "Sorry, there was an error uploading your file.";
                $status = "error";
            }
        }
    } else {
        $message = "No file was uploaded or there was an upload error.";
        $status = "error";
    }
}

header("Location: upload_form.html?message=$message&status=$status");
exit();
?>

































OUTPUT:


















Exp No: 21 PHP with MySQL Develop a simple application to -
