Exp No: 22 Create a PHP page for login page with sql connection.
CREATE_LOGIN_TABLE.PHP

INPUT:
<?php
$servername = "localhost:3507";
$username = "root";
$password = ""; 
$database = "login_db";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $database);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// Create table
$sql = "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
)";

if ($conn->query($sql) === TRUE) {
    echo "Table created successfully";
} else {
    echo "Error creating table: " . $conn->error;
}

// Insert a sample user
$sample_user = "INSERT INTO users (username, password) VALUES ('testuser', '" . password_hash("testpassword", PASSWORD_DEFAULT) . "')";
if ($conn->query($sample_user) === TRUE) {
    echo "Sample user inserted successfully";
} else {
    echo "Error inserting sample user: " . $conn->error;
}

// Close connection
$conn->close();
?>

LOGIN.HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Login</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f5f5dc;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        h2 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #8a2be2;
            font-size: 2em;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        form {
            max-width: 300px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }
        input[type="text"], input[type="password"] {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 8px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        input[type="submit"] {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #8a2be2;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        input[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #7a1dc4;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Login</h2>
    <form action="login.php" method="post">
        <label for="username">Username:</label>
        <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
        <label for="password">Password:</label>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
</body>
</html>
LOGIN.PHP
<?php
$servername = "localhost:3507";
$username = "root";
$password = ""; // Your MySQL root password, if you have set one
$database = "login_db";

// Create connection
$conn = mysqli_connect($servername, $username, $password, $database);

// Check connection
if (!$conn) {
    die("Connection failed: " . mysqli_connect_error());
}

// Collect form data
$user = $_POST['username'];
$pass = $_POST['password'];

// Query to check if the user exists
$sql = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='$user' AND password='$pass'";
$result = mysqli_query($conn, $sql);

if (mysqli_num_rows($result) > 0) {
    echo "Login successful! Welcome, " . $user;
} else {
    echo "Invalid username or password.";
}

mysqli_close($conn);
?>







































OUTPUT :
























Exp No: 23 File Handling Using PHP
 a. Write a php program to Read from an existing file. 
b. Write a php program to Write a file

INPUT :

WRITE.PHP
<?php
// Open the file for writing
$filename = "example.txt";
$file = fopen($filename, "w") or die("Unable to open file!");

// Text to write to the file
$text = "HELLO THIS IS SHIKHAR AGARWAL";

// Write the text to the file
fwrite($file, $text);

// Close the file
fclose($file);
echo "Data written to $filename successfully!";
?>
READ.PHP
<?php
// Open the file for reading
$filename = "example.txt";
$file = fopen($filename, "r") or die("Unable to open file!");

// Read and output the file line by line
while (!feof($file)) {
    echo fgets($file) . "\n";
}

// Close the file
fclose($file);
?>








OUTPUT :




















Exp No: 24 In jQuery, write a program to hide , show or toggle on click function.

INPUT :
 <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>jQuery Hide, Show, and Toggle</title>
    
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
            // Hide the element
            $("#hideButton").click(function() {
                $("#content").hide();
            });

            // Show the element
            $("#showButton").click(function() {
                $("#content").show();
            });

            // Toggle the element
            $("#toggleButton").click(function() {
                $("#content").toggle();
            });
        });
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>jQuery Hide, Show, and Toggle </h1>
    <div id="content" style="padding: 10px; background-color: lightgray;">
        This is the content that will be hidden, shown, or toggled.
    </div>
    <br>
    <button id="hideButton">Hide</button>
    <button id="showButton">Show</button>
    <button id="toggleButton">Toggle</button>
</body>
</html>




OUTPUT :






